In California, a shark injured a 13-year-old diver who fished for lobster
According to official sources, on Saturday, the first day of the lobster hunting season, a 13-year-old diver in California was attacked by a shark and injured.
The attack occurred around 7 a.m. near Beacon Beach in Encinitas.
As Chad Hammel told in an interview with KSWB-TV station (San Diego), on Saturday morning he dived with friends and about half an hour later heard the boy’s cries for help. Together with friends, they sailed by boat to the scene of the attack and pulled the teenager out of the water.
According to Hammel, at first he decided that the boy was loudly pleased with the capture of the lobster, but quickly "understood that he was shouting 'I was bitten!
I was bitten!”
